<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 10:01PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of central Blaine
County through 1045 PM MDT...
At 1001 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 18
miles northwest of Hays, or 25 miles northwest of Zortman, moving
east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Harlem, Fort Belknap and Cleveland.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
